% references.bib --- diagnostic-validity (project-local, VERIFIED-ONLY).
%
% DELIBERATELY NOT a symlink to the central house-style bib, and this
% project does NOT keep a separate references-local.bib. This overrides the
% portfolio-wide bib workflow (symlink-to-central + references-local) on
% purpose:
%
%   The verified-only invariant is the fabrication firewall. biber can only
%   resolve a key that has passed through TO_VERIFY.md and been promoted
%   here by the pm node. An unverified \cite therefore FAILS LOUDLY at
%   compile time instead of silently resolving against the thousands of
%   entries in the central bib. The repo also stays self-contained for
%   handoff. Duplicating a handful of central entries here is the accepted
%   cost (pm-update, 2026-06-10).
%
% Executor: add citation candidates to TO_VERIFY.md only. The pm node
% promotes verified entries into THIS file (CLAUDE.md rules 1-2; PLAN §7
% rule 2).
%
% Entries below are copied verbatim from the central, verified bib
% (.house-style/references.bib) except cgel2002 and goodman1955, which use
% project-internal keys (= central huddleston2002 and Goodman1955) so
% main.tex needs no key changes. NOTE: whiterawlins2016 / whiterawlins2020
% are cited in main.tex but are NOT yet here -- they are read and logged in
% TO_VERIFY.md (items 1-2) and await pm promotion in Phase 2; until then the
% build fails loudly on those keys, which is the firewall working.

